-- Russian Central Bank Gold Holdings Reach Post-Soviet Record $28.2 Billion
-- Paul Abelsky
-- 2010-07-07T07:27:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/russian-central-bank-gold-holdings-reach-post-soviet-record-28-2-billion.html

          
          
             Russia’s central bank said the value
of its gold holdings advanced 2.8 percent last month to $28.2
billion, in an e-mailed statement today.  
 That’s the highest level since Bank Rossii started
reporting the value of its gold holdings in 1993.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Abelsky in Moscow at 
 pabelsky@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        